ciscoDiameterBasePMIB.name: ciscoDiameterBasePMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoDiameterBasePMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-aaa@cisco.com
ciscoDiameterBasePMIB.description: The MIB module for entities implementing the Diameter Base Protocol. Initial Cisco'ized version of the IETF draft draft-zorn-dime-diameter-base-protocol-mib-00.txt.

ciscoDiaBaseProtEnableProtocolErrorNotif.name: ciscoDiaBaseProtEnableProtocolErrorNotif
ciscoDiaBaseProtEnableProtocolErrorNotif.description: Setting the value of this object to true(1) enables the ciscoDiaBaseProtProtocolErrorNotif notification.

ciscoDiaBaseProtProtocolErrorNotif.name: ciscoDiaBaseProtProtocolErrorNotif
ciscoDiaBaseProtProtocolErrorNotif.description: An ciscoDiaBaseProtProtocolErrorNotif notification is sent when both the following conditions are true: 1) the value of ciscoDiaBaseProtEnableProtocolErrorNotif is true(1) 2) the value of cdbpPeerStatsProtocolErrors changes. It can be utilized by an NMS to trigger logical/physical entity table maintenance polls.

ciscoDiaBaseProtEnableTransientFailureNo.name: ciscoDiaBaseProtEnableTransientFailureNotif
ciscoDiaBaseProtEnableTransientFailureNo.description: Setting the value of this object to true(1) enables the ciscoDiaBaseProtTransientFailureNotif notification.

ciscoDiaBaseProtTransientFailureNotif.name: ciscoDiaBaseProtTransientFailureNotif
ciscoDiaBaseProtTransientFailureNotif.description: An ciscoDiaBaseProtTransientFailureNotif notification is sent when both the following conditions are true: 1) the value of ciscoDiaBaseProtEnableTransientFailureNotif is true(1) 2) the value of cdbpPeerStatsTransientFailures changes. It can be utilized by an NMS to trigger logical/physical entity table maintenance polls.

ciscoDiaBaseProtEnablePermanentFailureNo.name: ciscoDiaBaseProtEnablePermanentFailureNotif
ciscoDiaBaseProtEnablePermanentFailureNo.description: Setting the value of this object to true(1) enables the ciscoDiaBaseProtPermanentFailureNotif notification.

ciscoDiaBaseProtPermanentFailureNotif.name: ciscoDiaBaseProtPermanentFailureNotif
ciscoDiaBaseProtPermanentFailureNotif.description: An ciscoDiaBaseProtPermanentFailureNotif notification is sent when both the following conditions are true: 1) the value of ciscoDiaBaseProtEnablePermanentFailureNotif is true(1) 2) the value of cdbpPeerStatsPermanentFailures changes. It can be utilized by an NMS to trigger logical/physical entity table maintenance polls.

ciscoDiaBaseProtEnablePeerConnectionDown.name: ciscoDiaBaseProtEnablePeerConnectionDownNotif
ciscoDiaBaseProtEnablePeerConnectionDown.description: Setting the value of this object to true(1) enables the ciscoDiaBaseProtPeerConnectionDownNotif notification.

ciscoDiaBaseProtPeerConnectionDownNotif.name: ciscoDiaBaseProtPeerConnectionDownNotif
ciscoDiaBaseProtPeerConnectionDownNotif.description: An ciscoDiaBaseProtPeerConnectionDownNotif notification is sent when both the following conditions are true: 1) the value of ciscoDiaBaseProtEnablePeerConnectionDownNotif is true(1) 2) cdbpPeerStatsState changes to closed(1). It can be utilized by an NMS to trigger logical/physical entity table maintenance polls.

ciscoDiaBaseProtEnablePeerConnectionUpNo.name: ciscoDiaBaseProtEnablePeerConnectionUpNotif
ciscoDiaBaseProtEnablePeerConnectionUpNo.description: Setting the value of this object to true(1) enables the ciscoDiaBaseProtPeerConnectionUpNotif notification.

ciscoDiaBaseProtPeerConnectionUpNotif.name: ciscoDiaBaseProtPeerConnectionUpNotif
ciscoDiaBaseProtPeerConnectionUpNotif.description: An ciscoDiaBaseProtPeerConnectionUpNotif notification is sent when both the following conditions are true: 1) the value of ciscoDiaBaseProtEnablePeerConnectionUpNotif is true(1) 2) the value of cdbpPeerStatsState changes to either rOpen(6)or iOpen(7). It can be utilized by an NMS to trigger logical/physical entity table maintenance polls.

cdbpLocalId.name: cdbpLocalId
cdbpLocalId.description: The implementation identification string for the Diameter software in use on the system, for example; 'diameterd'

cdbpLocalIpAddrTable.name: cdbpLocalIpAddrTable
cdbpLocalIpAddrTable.description: The table listing the Diameter local host's IP Addresses.

cdbpLocalIpAddrEntry.name: cdbpLocalIpAddrEntry
cdbpLocalIpAddrEntry.description: A row entry representing a Diameter local host IP Address.

cdbpLocalIpAddrIndex.name: cdbpLocalIpAddrIndex
cdbpLocalIpAddrIndex.description: A number uniquely identifying the number of IP Addresses supported by this Diameter host.

cdbpLocalIpAddrType.name: cdbpLocalIpAddrType
cdbpLocalIpAddrType.description: The type of internet address stored in cdbpLocalIpAddress.

cdbpLocalIpAddress.name: cdbpLocalIpAddress
cdbpLocalIpAddress.description: The IP-Address of the host, which is of the type specified in cdbpLocalIpAddrType.

cdbpLocalTcpListenPort.name: cdbpLocalTcpListenPort
cdbpLocalTcpListenPort.description: This object represents Diameter TCP 'listen' port.

cdbpLocalSctpListenPort.name: cdbpLocalSctpListenPort
cdbpLocalSctpListenPort.description: This object represents Diameter SCTP 'listen' port.

cdbpLocalOriginHost.name: cdbpLocalOriginHost
cdbpLocalOriginHost.description: This object represents the Local Origin Host.

cdbpLocalRealm.name: cdbpLocalRealm
cdbpLocalRealm.description: This object represents the Local Realm Name.

cdbpRedundancyEnabled.name: cdbpRedundancyEnabled
cdbpRedundancyEnabled.description: This parameter indicates if cisco redundancy has been enabled, it is enabled if set to true and disabled if set to false.

cdbpRedundancyInfraState.name: cdbpRedundancyInfraState
cdbpRedundancyInfraState.description: This parameter indicates the current state of cisco redundancy infrastructure state. rfUnknown(0) - unknown state rfDisabled(1) - RF is not functioning at this time rfInitialization(2) - co-ordinating init with platform rfNegotiation(3) - initial negotiation with peer to determine active-standby rfStandbyCold(4) - peer is active, we're cold rfStandbyConfig(5) - sync config from active to standby rfStandbyFileSys(6) - sync file sys from active to standby rfStandbyBulk(7) - clients bulk sync from active to standby rfStandbyHot(8) - standby ready-n-able to be active rfActiveFast(9) - immediate notification of standby going active rfActiveDrain(10) - drain queued messages from peer rfActivePreconfig(11) - active and before config rfActivePostconfig(12) - active and post config rfActive(13) - actively processing new calls rfActiveExtraload(14) - actively processing new calls extra resources other Processing is failed and I have extra load.

cdbpRedundancyLastSwitchover.name: cdbpRedundancyLastSwitchover
cdbpRedundancyLastSwitchover.description: This object represents the Last Switchover Time.

cdbpLocalApplTable.name: cdbpLocalApplTable
cdbpLocalApplTable.description: The table listing the Diameter applications supported by this server.

cdbpLocalApplEntry.name: cdbpLocalApplEntry
cdbpLocalApplEntry.description: A row entry representing a Diameter application on this server.

cdbpLocalApplIndex.name: cdbpLocalApplIndex
cdbpLocalApplIndex.description: A number uniquely identifying a supported Diameter application. Upon reload, cdbpLocalApplIndex values may be changed.

cdbpLocalApplStorageType.name: cdbpLocalApplStorageType
cdbpLocalApplStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row. None of the columnar objects is writable when the conceptual row is permanent.

cdbpLocalApplRowStatus.name: cdbpLocalApplRowStatus
cdbpLocalApplRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to either createAndGo(4) or createAndWait(5). Until instances of all corresponding columns are appropriately configured, the value of the corresponding instance of the cdsgStatus column is 'notReady'. In particular, a newly created row cannot be made active until the corresponding cdbpLocalApplIndex has been set. cdbpLocalApplIndex may not be modified while the value of this object is active(1): An attempt to set these objects while the value of cdbpLocalApplStatus is active(1) will result in an inconsistentValue error. Entries in this table with cdbpLocalApplStatus equal to active(1) remain in the table until destroyed. Entries in this table with cdbpLocalApplStatus equal to values other than active(1) will be destroyed after timeout (5 minutes).

cdbpLocalVendorTable.name: cdbpLocalVendorTable
cdbpLocalVendorTable.description: The table listing the vendor IDs supported by local Diameter.

cdbpLocalVendorEntry.name: cdbpLocalVendorEntry
cdbpLocalVendorEntry.description: A row entry representing a vendor ID supported by local Diameter.

cdbpLocalVendorIndex.name: cdbpLocalVendorIndex
cdbpLocalVendorIndex.description: A number uniquely identifying the vendor ID supported by local Diameter. Upon reload, cdbpLocalVendorIndex values may be changed.

cdbpLocalVendorId.name: cdbpLocalVendorId
cdbpLocalVendorId.description: The active vendor ID used for peer connections. diameterVendorIetf(0) - Diameter vendor id ietf diameterVendorCisco(9) - Diameter vendor id cisco diameterVendor3gpp(10415) - Diameter vendor id 3gpp diameterVendorVodafone(12645) - Diameter vendor id vodafone.

cdbpLocalVendorStorageType.name: cdbpLocalVendorStorageType
cdbpLocalVendorStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row. None of the objects are writable when the conceptual row is permanent.

cdbpLocalVendorRowStatus.name: cdbpLocalVendorRowStatus
cdbpLocalVendorRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to either createAndGo(4) or createAndWait(5). Until instances of all corresponding columns are appropriately configured, the value of the corresponding instance of the cdbpLocalVendorRowStatus column is 'notReady'. In particular, a newly created row cannot be made active until the corresponding cdbpLocalVendorId has been set. cdbpLocalVendorId may not be modified while the value of this object is active(1): An attempt to set these objects while the value of cdbpLocalVendorRowStatus is active(1) will result in an inconsistentValue error. Entries in this table with cdbpLocalVendorRowStatus equal to active(1) remain in the table until destroyed. Entries in this table with cdbpLocalVendorRowStatus equal to values other than active(1) will be destroyed after timeout (5 minutes).

cdbpAppAdvToPeerTable.name: cdbpAppAdvToPeerTable
cdbpAppAdvToPeerTable.description: The table listing the applications advertised by this host to each peer and the types of service supported: accounting, authentication or both.

cdbpAppAdvToPeerEntry.name: cdbpAppAdvToPeerEntry
cdbpAppAdvToPeerEntry.description: A row entry representing a discovered or configured Diameter peer server.

cdbpAppAdvToPeerVendorId.name: cdbpAppAdvToPeerVendorId
cdbpAppAdvToPeerVendorId.description: The IANA Enterprise Code value assigned to the vendor of the Diameter device.

cdbpAppAdvToPeerIndex.name: cdbpAppAdvToPeerIndex
cdbpAppAdvToPeerIndex.description: A number uniquely identifying the Diameter applications advertised as supported by this host to each peer. Upon reload, cdbpAppAdvToPeerIndex values may be changed.

cdbpAppAdvToPeerServices.name: cdbpAppAdvToPeerServices
cdbpAppAdvToPeerServices.description: The type of services supported for each application, accounting, authentication or both. acct(1) - accounting auth(2) - authentication both(3) - both accounting and authentication.

cdbpAppAdvToPeerStorageType.name: cdbpAppAdvToPeerStorageType
cdbpAppAdvToPeerStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row. None of the objects are writable when the conceptual row is permanent.

cdbpAppAdvToPeerRowStatus.name: cdbpAppAdvToPeerRowStatus
cdbpAppAdvToPeerRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to either createAndGo(4) or createAndWait(5). Until instances of all corresponding columns are appropriately configured, the value of the corresponding instance of the cdbpAppAdvToPeerRowStatus column is 'notReady'. In particular, a newly created row cannot be made active until the corresponding cdbpAppAdvToPeerVendorId has been set. cdbpAppAdvToPeerVendorId may not be modified while the value of this object is active(1): An attempt to set these objects while the value of cdbpAppAdvToPeerRowStatus is active(1) will result in an inconsistentValue error. Entries in this table with cdbpAppAdvToPeerRowStatus equal to active(1) remain in the table until destroyed. Entries in this table with cdbpAppAdvToPeerRowStatus equal to values other than active(1) will be destroyed after timeout (5 minutes).

cdbpLocalStatsTotalPacketsIn.name: cdbpLocalStatsTotalPacketsIn
cdbpLocalStatsTotalPacketsIn.description: The total number of packets received by Diameter Base Protocol.

cdbpLocalStatsTotalPacketsOut.name: cdbpLocalStatsTotalPacketsOut
cdbpLocalStatsTotalPacketsOut.description: The total number of packets transmitted by Diameter Base Protocol.

cdbpLocalStatsTotalUpTime.name: cdbpLocalStatsTotalUpTime
cdbpLocalStatsTotalUpTime.description: This object represents the total time the Diameter server has been up until now.

cdbpLocalResetTime.name: cdbpLocalResetTime
cdbpLocalResetTime.description: If the server keeps persistent state (e.g., a process) and supports a 'reset' operation (e.g., can be told to re-read configuration files), this value will be the time elapsed (in hundredths of a second) since the server was 'reset'. For software that does not have persistence or does not support a 'reset' operation, this value will be zero.

cdbpLocalConfigReset.name: cdbpLocalConfigReset
cdbpLocalConfigReset.description: Status/action object to reinitialize any persistent server state. When set to reset(2), any persistent server state (such as a process) is reinitialized as if the server had just been started. This value will never be returned by a read operation. When read, one of the following values will be returned: other(1) - server in some unknown state. reset(2) - command to reinitialize server state. initializing(3) - server (re)initializing. running(4) - server currently running.

cdbpPeerTable.name: cdbpPeerTable
cdbpPeerTable.description: The table listing information regarding the discovered or configured Diameter peer servers.

cdbpPeerEntry.name: cdbpPeerEntry
cdbpPeerEntry.description: A row entry representing a discovered or configured Diameter peer server.

cdbpPeerIndex.name: cdbpPeerIndex
cdbpPeerIndex.description: A number uniquely identifying each Diameter peer with which the host server communicates. Upon reload, cdbpPeerIndex values may be changed.

cdbpPeerId.name: cdbpPeerId
cdbpPeerId.description: The server identifier for the Diameter peer. It must be unique and non-empty.

cdbpPeerPortConnect.name: cdbpPeerPortConnect
cdbpPeerPortConnect.description: The connection port this server used to connect to the Diameter peer. If there is no active connection, this value will be zero(0).

cdbpPeerPortListen.name: cdbpPeerPortListen
cdbpPeerPortListen.description: The port the server is listening on.

cdbpPeerProtocol.name: cdbpPeerProtocol
cdbpPeerProtocol.description: The transport protocol (tcp/sctp) the Diameter peer is using. tcp(1) - Transmission Control Protocol sctp(2) - Stream Control Transmission Protocol.

cdbpPeerSecurity.name: cdbpPeerSecurity
cdbpPeerSecurity.description: The security the Diameter peer is using. other(1) - Unknown Security Protocol. tls(2) - Transport Layer Security Protocol. ipsec(3) - Internet Protocol Security.

cdbpPeerFirmwareRevision.name: cdbpPeerFirmwareRevision
cdbpPeerFirmwareRevision.description: Firmware revision of peer. If no firmware revision, the revision of the Diameter software module may be reported instead.

cdbpPeerStorageType.name: cdbpPeerStorageType
cdbpPeerStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row. Only cdbpPeerPortListen object is writable when the conceptual row is permanent.

cdbpPeerRowStatus.name: cdbpPeerRowStatus
cdbpPeerRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to either createAndGo(4) or createAndWait(5). Until instances of all corresponding columns are appropriately configured, the value of the corresponding instance of the cdbpPeerRowStatus column is 'notReady'. In particular, a newly created row cannot be made active until the corresponding cdbpPeerId has been set. cdbpPeerId may not be modified while the value of this object is active(1): An attempt to set these objects while the value of cdbpPeerRowStatus is active(1) will result in an inconsistentValue error. Entries in this table with cdbpPeerRowStatus equal to active(1) remain in the table until destroyed. Entries in this table with cdbpPeerRowStatus equal to values other than active(1) will be destroyed after timeout (5 minutes).

cdbpPeerIpAddrTable.name: cdbpPeerIpAddrTable
cdbpPeerIpAddrTable.description: The table listing the Diameter server IP Addresses.

cdbpPeerIpAddrEntry.name: cdbpPeerIpAddrEntry
cdbpPeerIpAddrEntry.description: A row entry representing peer Diameter server IP Addresses.

cdbpPeerIpAddressIndex.name: cdbpPeerIpAddressIndex
cdbpPeerIpAddressIndex.description: A number uniquely identifying the number of IP Addresses supported by all Diameter peers.

cdbpPeerIpAddressType.name: cdbpPeerIpAddressType
cdbpPeerIpAddressType.description: The type of address stored in diameterPeerIpAddress.

cdbpPeerIpAddress.name: cdbpPeerIpAddress
cdbpPeerIpAddress.description: The active IP Address(es) used for connections.

cdbpAppAdvFromPeerTable.name: cdbpAppAdvFromPeerTable
cdbpAppAdvFromPeerTable.description: The table listing the applications advertised by each peer to this host and the types of service supported: accounting, authentication or both.

cdbpAppAdvFromPeerEntry.name: cdbpAppAdvFromPeerEntry
cdbpAppAdvFromPeerEntry.description: A row entry representing a discovered or configured Diameter peer server.

cdbpAppAdvFromPeerVendorId.name: cdbpAppAdvFromPeerVendorId
cdbpAppAdvFromPeerVendorId.description: The IANA Enterprise Code value assigned to the vendor of the Diameter device.

cdbpAppAdvFromPeerIndex.name: cdbpAppAdvFromPeerIndex
cdbpAppAdvFromPeerIndex.description: A number uniquely identifying the applications advertised as supported from each Diameter peer.

cdbpAppAdvFromPeerType.name: cdbpAppAdvFromPeerType
cdbpAppAdvFromPeerType.description: The type of services supported for each application, accounting, authentication or both. acct(1) - accounting auth(2) - authentication both(3) - both accounting and authentication.

cdbpPeerVendorTable.name: cdbpPeerVendorTable
cdbpPeerVendorTable.description: The table listing the Vendor IDs supported by the peer.

cdbpPeerVendorEntry.name: cdbpPeerVendorEntry
cdbpPeerVendorEntry.description: A row entry representing a Vendor ID supported by the peer.

cdbpPeerVendorIndex.name: cdbpPeerVendorIndex
cdbpPeerVendorIndex.description: A number uniquely identifying the Vendor ID supported by the peer. Upon reload, cdbpPeerVendorIndex values may be changed.

cdbpPeerVendorId.name: cdbpPeerVendorId
cdbpPeerVendorId.description: The active vendor ID used for peer connections. diameterVendorIetf(0) - Diameter vendor id ietf diameterVendorCisco(9) - Diameter vendor id cisco diameterVendor3gpp(10415) - Diameter vendor id 3gpp diameterVendorVodafone(12645) - Diameter vendor id vodafone.

cdbpPeerVendorStorageType.name: cdbpPeerVendorStorageType
cdbpPeerVendorStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row. None of the objects are writable when the conceptual row is permanent.

cdbpPeerVendorRowStatus.name: cdbpPeerVendorRowStatus
cdbpPeerVendorRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to either createAndGo(4) or createAndWait(5). Until instances of all corresponding columns are appropriately configured, the value of the corresponding instance of the cdbpPeerVendorRowStatus column is 'notReady'. In particular, a newly created row cannot be made active until the corresponding cdbpPeerVendorId has been set. Also, a newly created row cannot be made active until the corresponding 'cdbpPeerIndex' has been set. cdbpPeerVendorId may not be modified while the value of this object is active(1): An attempt to set these objects while the value of cdbpPeerVendorRowStatus is active(1) will result in an inconsistentValue error. Entries in this table with cdbpPeerVendorRowStatus equal to active(1) remain in the table until destroyed. Entries in this table with cdbpPeerVendorRowStatus equal to values other than active(1) will be destroyed after timeout (5 minutes).

cdbpPeerStatsTable.name: cdbpPeerStatsTable
cdbpPeerStatsTable.description: The table listing the Diameter peer statistics.

cdbpPeerStatsEntry.name: cdbpPeerStatsEntry
cdbpPeerStatsEntry.description: A row entry representing a Diameter peer.

cdbpPeerStatsState.name: cdbpPeerStatsState
cdbpPeerStatsState.description: Connection state in the Peer State Machine of the peer with which this Diameter server is communicating. closed(1) - Connection closed with this peer. waitConnAck(2) - Waiting for an acknowledgment from this peer. waitICEA(3) - Waiting for a Capabilities-Exchange- Answer from this peer. elect(4) - When the peer and the server are both trying to bring up a connection with each other at the same time. An election process begins which determines which socket remains open. waitReturns(5) - Waiting for election returns. r-open(6) - Responder transport connection is used for communication. i-open(7) - Initiator transport connection is used for communication. closing(8) - Actively closing and doing cleanup.

cdbpPeerStatsStateDuration.name: cdbpPeerStatsStateDuration
cdbpPeerStatsStateDuration.description: This object represents the Peer state duration.

cdbpPeerStatsLastDiscCause.name: cdbpPeerStatsLastDiscCause
cdbpPeerStatsLastDiscCause.description: The last cause for a peers disconnection. rebooting(1) - A scheduled reboot is imminent. busy(2) - The peer's internal resources are constrained, and it has determined that the transport connection needs to be shutdown. doNotWantToTalk(3) - The peer has determined that it does not see a need for the transport connection to exist, since it does not expect any messages to be exchanged in the foreseeable future. electionLost(4) - The peer has determined that it has lost the election process and has therefore disconnected the transport connection.

cdbpPeerStatsWhoInitDisconnect.name: cdbpPeerStatsWhoInitDisconnect
cdbpPeerStatsWhoInitDisconnect.description: Did the host or peer initiate the disconnect? host(1) - If this server initiated the disconnect. peer(2) - If the peer with which this server was connected initiated the disconnect.

cdbpPeerStatsDWCurrentStatus.name: cdbpPeerStatsDWCurrentStatus
cdbpPeerStatsDWCurrentStatus.description: This object indicates the connection status. okay(1) - Indicates the connection is presumed working. suspect(2) - Indicates the connection is possibly congested or down. down(3) - The peer is no longer reachable, causing the transport connection to be shutdown. reopen(4) - Three watchdog messages are exchanged with accepted round trip times, and the connection to the peer is considered stabilized.

cdbpPeerStatsTimeoutConnAtmpts.name: cdbpPeerStatsTimeoutConnAtmpts
cdbpPeerStatsTimeoutConnAtmpts.description: If there is no transport connection with a peer, this is the number of times the server attempts to connect to that peer. This is reset on disconnection.

cdbpPeerStatsASRsIn.name: cdbpPeerStatsASRsIn
cdbpPeerStatsASRsIn.description: Abort-Session-Request messages received from the peer.

cdbpPeerStatsASRsOut.name: cdbpPeerStatsASRsOut
cdbpPeerStatsASRsOut.description: Abort-Session-Request messages sent to the peer.

cdbpPeerStatsASAsIn.name: cdbpPeerStatsASAsIn
cdbpPeerStatsASAsIn.description: Number of Abort-Session-Answer messages received from the peer.

cdbpPeerStatsASAsOut.name: cdbpPeerStatsASAsOut
cdbpPeerStatsASAsOut.description: Number of Abort-Session-Answer messages sent to the peer.

cdbpPeerStatsACRsIn.name: cdbpPeerStatsACRsIn
cdbpPeerStatsACRsIn.description: Number of Accounting-Request messages received from the peer.

cdbpPeerStatsACRsOut.name: cdbpPeerStatsACRsOut
cdbpPeerStatsACRsOut.description: Number of Accounting-Request messages sent to the peer.

cdbpPeerStatsACAsIn.name: cdbpPeerStatsACAsIn
cdbpPeerStatsACAsIn.description: Number of Accounting-Answer messages received from the peer.

cdbpPeerStatsACAsOut.name: cdbpPeerStatsACAsOut
cdbpPeerStatsACAsOut.description: Number of Accounting-Answer messages sent to the peer.

cdbpPeerStatsCERsIn.name: cdbpPeerStatsCERsIn
cdbpPeerStatsCERsIn.description: Number of Capabilities-Exchange-Request messages received from the peer.

cdbpPeerStatsCERsOut.name: cdbpPeerStatsCERsOut
cdbpPeerStatsCERsOut.description: Number of Capabilities-Exchange-Request messages sent to the peer.

cdbpPeerStatsCEAsIn.name: cdbpPeerStatsCEAsIn
cdbpPeerStatsCEAsIn.description: Number of Capabilities-Exchange-Answer messages received from the peer.

cdbpPeerStatsCEAsOut.name: cdbpPeerStatsCEAsOut
cdbpPeerStatsCEAsOut.description: Number of Capabilities-Exchange-Answer messages sent to the peer.

cdbpPeerStatsDWRsIn.name: cdbpPeerStatsDWRsIn
cdbpPeerStatsDWRsIn.description: Number of Device-Watchdog-Request messages received from the peer.

cdbpPeerStatsDWRsOut.name: cdbpPeerStatsDWRsOut
cdbpPeerStatsDWRsOut.description: Number of Device-Watchdog-Request messages sent to the peer.

cdbpPeerStatsDWAsIn.name: cdbpPeerStatsDWAsIn
cdbpPeerStatsDWAsIn.description: Number of Device-Watchdog-Answer messages received from the peer.

cdbpPeerStatsDWAsOut.name: cdbpPeerStatsDWAsOut
cdbpPeerStatsDWAsOut.description: Number of Device-Watchdog-Answer messages sent to the peer.

cdbpPeerStatsSTRsIn.name: cdbpPeerStatsSTRsIn
cdbpPeerStatsSTRsIn.description: Number of Session-Termination-Request messages received from the peer.

cdbpPeerStatsSTRsOut.name: cdbpPeerStatsSTRsOut
cdbpPeerStatsSTRsOut.description: Number of Session-Termination-Request messages sent to the peer.

cdbpPeerStatsSTAsIn.name: cdbpPeerStatsSTAsIn
cdbpPeerStatsSTAsIn.description: Number of Session-Termination-Answer messages received from the peer.

cdbpPeerStatsSTAsOut.name: cdbpPeerStatsSTAsOut
cdbpPeerStatsSTAsOut.description: Number of Session-Termination-Answer messages sent to the peer.

cdbpPeerStatsDWReqTimer.name: cdbpPeerStatsDWReqTimer
cdbpPeerStatsDWReqTimer.description: Device-Watchdog Request Timer, which is the interval between packets sent to peers.

cdbpPeerStatsRedirectEvents.name: cdbpPeerStatsRedirectEvents
cdbpPeerStatsRedirectEvents.description: Redirect Event count, which is the number of redirects sent from a peer.

cdbpPeerStatsAccDupRequests.name: cdbpPeerStatsAccDupRequests
cdbpPeerStatsAccDupRequests.description: The number of duplicate Diameter Accounting-Request packets received.

cdbpPeerStatsMalformedReqsts.name: cdbpPeerStatsMalformedReqsts
cdbpPeerStatsMalformedReqsts.description: The number of malformed Diameter packets received.

cdbpPeerStatsAccsNotRecorded.name: cdbpPeerStatsAccsNotRecorded
cdbpPeerStatsAccsNotRecorded.description: The number of Diameter Accounting-Request packets which were received and responded to but not recorded.

cdbpPeerStatsAccRetrans.name: cdbpPeerStatsAccRetrans
cdbpPeerStatsAccRetrans.description: The number of Diameter Accounting-Request packets retransmitted to this Diameter server.

cdbpPeerStatsTotalRetrans.name: cdbpPeerStatsTotalRetrans
cdbpPeerStatsTotalRetrans.description: The number of Diameter packets retransmitted to this Diameter server, not to include Diameter Accounting-Request packets retransmitted.

cdbpPeerStatsAccPendReqstsOut.name: cdbpPeerStatsAccPendReqstsOut
cdbpPeerStatsAccPendReqstsOut.description: The number of Diameter Accounting-Request packets sent to this peer that have not yet timed out or received a response. This variable is incremented when an Accounting-Request is sent to this server and decremented due to receipt of an Accounting-Response, a timeout or a retransmission.

cdbpPeerStatsAccReqstsDropped.name: cdbpPeerStatsAccReqstsDropped
cdbpPeerStatsAccReqstsDropped.description: The number of Accounting-Requests to this server that have been dropped.

cdbpPeerStatsHByHDropMessages.name: cdbpPeerStatsHByHDropMessages
cdbpPeerStatsHByHDropMessages.description: An answer message that is received with an unknown hop-by-hop identifier. Does not include accounting requests dropped.

cdbpPeerStatsEToEDupMessages.name: cdbpPeerStatsEToEDupMessages
cdbpPeerStatsEToEDupMessages.description: Duplicate answer messages that are to be locally consumed. Does not include duplicate accounting requests received.

cdbpPeerStatsUnknownTypes.name: cdbpPeerStatsUnknownTypes
cdbpPeerStatsUnknownTypes.description: The number of Diameter packets of unknown type which were received.

cdbpPeerStatsProtocolErrors.name: cdbpPeerStatsProtocolErrors
cdbpPeerStatsProtocolErrors.description: This object represents the Number of protocol errors returned to peer, but not including redirects.

cdbpPeerStatsTransientFailures.name: cdbpPeerStatsTransientFailures
cdbpPeerStatsTransientFailures.description: This object represents the transient failure count.

cdbpPeerStatsPermanentFailures.name: cdbpPeerStatsPermanentFailures
cdbpPeerStatsPermanentFailures.description: This object represents the Number of permanent failures returned to peer.

cdbpPeerStatsTransportDown.name: cdbpPeerStatsTransportDown
cdbpPeerStatsTransportDown.description: This object represents the Number of unexpected transport failures.

cdbpRealmKnownPeersTable.name: cdbpRealmKnownPeersTable
cdbpRealmKnownPeersTable.description: The table listing the Diameter realms and known peers.

cdbpRealmKnownPeersEntry.name: cdbpRealmKnownPeersEntry
cdbpRealmKnownPeersEntry.description: A row entry representing a Diameter realm and known peers.

cdbpRealmKnownPeersIndex.name: cdbpRealmKnownPeersIndex
cdbpRealmKnownPeersIndex.description: A number uniquely identifying a peer known to this realm. Upon reload, cdbpRealmKnownPeersIndex values may be changed.

cdbpRealmKnownPeers.name: cdbpRealmKnownPeers
cdbpRealmKnownPeers.description: The index of the peer this realm knows about. This is an ordered list, where the ordering signifies the order in which the peers are tried. Same as the cdbpPeerIndex

cdbpRealmKnownPeersChosen.name: cdbpRealmKnownPeersChosen
cdbpRealmKnownPeersChosen.description: How the realm chooses which peer to send packets to. roundRobin(1) - The peer used for each transaction is selected based on the order in which peers are configured. loadBalance(2) - The peer used for each transaction is based on the load metric (maybe implementation dependent) of all peers defined for the realm, with the least loaded server selected first. firstPreferred(3) - The first defined server is always used for transactions unless failover occurs. mostRecentFirst(4) - The most recently used server is used first for each transaction.

cdbpRealmMessageRouteIndex.name: cdbpRealmMessageRouteIndex
cdbpRealmMessageRouteIndex.description: A number uniquely identifying each realm.

cdbpRealmMessageRouteRealm.name: cdbpRealmMessageRouteRealm
cdbpRealmMessageRouteRealm.description: This object represents the realm name

cdbpRealmMessageRouteApp.name: cdbpRealmMessageRouteApp
cdbpRealmMessageRouteApp.description: Application id used to route packets to this realm.

cdbpRealmMessageRouteType.name: cdbpRealmMessageRouteType
cdbpRealmMessageRouteType.description: The types of service supported for each realm application: accounting, authentication or both. acct(1) - accounting auth(2) - authentication both(3) - both accounting and authentication.

cdbpRealmMessageRouteAction.name: cdbpRealmMessageRouteAction
cdbpRealmMessageRouteAction.description: The action is used to identify how a message should be treated based on the realm, application and type. local(1) - Diameter messages that resolve to a route entry with the Local Action set to Local can be satisfied locally, and do not need to be routed to another server. relay(2) - All Diameter messages that fall within this category MUST be routed to a next-hop server, without modifying any non-routing AVPs. proxy(3) - All Diameter messages that fall within this category MUST be routed to a next-hop server. redirect(4) - Diameter messages that fall within this category MUST have the identity of the home Diameter server(s) appended, and returned to the sender of the message.
